    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>The following solution works in IntelliJ IDEA 2021.3:</strong></p>\n<p>To find unused functions in <strong>JavaScript and Typescript</strong> code, use the <strong>Unused global symbol</strong> inspection.</p>\n<h3>Running the Inspection</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Open the <strong>Run Inspection by Name</strong> window with the shortcut <code>Ctrl+Alt+Shift+I</code> (Windows/Linux) or <code>Cmd+Shift+I</code> (Mac). You can also use the menu <strong>Code &gt; Analyze Code &gt; Run Inspection by Name...</strong></li>\n<li>Type <strong>&quot;Unused global symbol&quot;</strong> in the search box and select the inspection from the list.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, choose a scope for your analysis, such as <strong>Whole project</strong> or a <strong>File</strong> (or whatever you want to choose).</li>\n<li>Click <strong>OK</strong> to run the inspection.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The results will appear in the <strong>Inspection Results</strong> tool window, listing all unused global functions and variables.</p>\n"
  } ],
